[The numbers continue to grow but vary dramatically related to the source of the data. In most outbreaks of cholera, the number of confirmed cases is relatively small compared to the total number probably infected. With about 4500 cases of "general" diarrhea, a significant number of these numbers may well be caused by _Vibrio cholerae_. - Mod.LL

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/1B7y.
